@node Installation
@chapter Installation

Cairog requires @uref{https://guix.gnu.org/, GNU Guix}.

@menu
* From Source::          Install directly from a local checkout.
* Via Guix Channel::     Install via the cairog channel.
* As a Dependency::      Declare cairog in your own Guix project.
@end menu

@node From Source
@section From Source

Clone the repository and install into your Guix profile:

@example
git clone https://github.com/zictogo/cairog
guix package -f cairog/guix.scm
@end example

@node Via Guix Channel
@section Via Guix Channel

Add the cairog channel to @file{~/.config/guix/channels.scm}:

@example
(cons* (channel
         (name 'cairog)
         (url "https://github.com/zictogo/cairog-channel"))
       %default-channels)
@end example

Then:

@example
guix pull
guix install cairog
@end example

@node As a Dependency
@section As a Dependency

After enabling the channel (@pxref{Via Guix Channel}), declare cairog
in your project's @file{guix.scm}:

@example
(use-modules (cairog packages)
             (guix packages)
             (guix build-system gnu)
             (gnu packages guile))

(package
  (name "my-project")
  ...
  (inputs (list cairog guile-3.0)))
@end example

In both cases the modules are available with no extra configuration:

@example
(use-modules (cairog))
@end example
